<MainLayout title="Ancient Text Recovery & Archaeology">
  <h1>III. Ancient Text Recovery & Archaeology</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-slate-500 -mt-4 mb-8 font-sans">Deciphering the Past with AI</p>

  <p>
    AI is enabling scholars to read texts that have been unreadable for millennia, from damaged
    inscriptions to carbonized scrolls. These breakthroughs represent some of the most dramatic
    success stories at the intersection of AI and humanities research.
  </p>

  <h2>Aeneas (DeepMind)</h2>

  <p>
    Google DeepMind's <strong>Aeneas</strong> system represents a major advance in computational
    epigraphy—the study of ancient inscriptions.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Capability</strong>: Dates Latin inscriptions within a decade of accuracy</li>
    <li><strong>Application</strong>: Helps scholars contextualize fragmentary or undated inscriptions</li>
    <li><strong>Methodology</strong>: Analyzes letter forms, vocabulary, and formulaic patterns</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The ability to date inscriptions with such precision has profound implications for understanding
    the evolution of Latin writing and Roman administrative practices.
  </p>

  <h2>The Vesuvius Challenge</h2>

  <p>
    Perhaps the most dramatic AI achievement in recent humanities research, the <strong>Vesuvius
    Challenge</strong> has unlocked texts that have remained unread for two thousand years.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Achievement</strong>: Revealed Greek text from 2,000-year-old carbonized scrolls</li>
    <li><strong>Source</strong>: Papyrus scrolls from Herculaneum, buried by the eruption of Mount Vesuvius in 79 CE</li>
    <li><strong>Method</strong>: Combines X-ray tomography with AI-powered ink detection and text recognition</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    These scrolls, too fragile to unroll without destruction, can now be "virtually unwrapped" and
    read using non-invasive imaging combined with machine learning—opening a window into an entire
    lost library of ancient philosophy.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose my-10 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 rounded-r-lg">
    <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-slate-800 mb-2">Key Takeaway</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700">
      AI is not merely accelerating existing research methods—it is enabling entirely new forms
      of discovery, recovering knowledge that was previously considered permanently lost.
    </p>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
